{"id": 78182846, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/saltstack/salt/issues/23927", "body": "We have a pattern where some states will also manage other states (boto_asg manages boto_lc, boto_elb manages boto_route53, pagerduty can manage boto_sns). We do this for syntactic sugar. For instance, boto_asg will create and destroy launch configurations automatically and associate them with the autoscale group.

Right now we're calling state.single, which actually works fine, except that it refreshes the modules every time it's called, which makes things incredibly slow.
